post_text:
This Friday at 5:30pm, Living Room Concert Series returns LIVE with a new local artist for you to listen to from your own home. Meet Mary Kelley -

Guitarist and vocalist Mary Kelley has played in a variety of bands: Rock ‘n Roll, Blues, Country, and Bluegrass. She plays mandolin and banjo as well as guitar. Her music hero is gypsy jazz guitarist Django Reinhardt. So many musicians have influenced Mary over the years: Django, Eric Clapton, Melissa Etheridge, Debbie Davies, Joe Bonamassa, Chrissie Hynde…the list is endless. Mary loves to sing and play, and most of all, to entertain her audience. She was given the nickname “Guitar Mary” by fellow musicians some years ago, when they realized she could hold her own playing lead guitar. “Guitar Mary” is the newest member of the Prescott-based band called The Tone Kings. Check out The Tone Kings on Facebook, at:
https://www.facebook.com/TONE-KINGS-121698962556040/

post_text:
Our musical artist playing Live in your Living Room this week is Dan Shaw.

Dan grew up in Phoenix Arizona and is a longtime resident of Prescott where his kids grew up. He toured Europe with the Phoenix Boys Choir. Dan minored in music in college and performed in the Opera. He toured with rock bands and stopped playing in 1980 to get married and raise a family. Dan got back into music after the kids all left for college. Dan enjoys singing harmonies and in the band He sings and plays guitars, dobro, banjo, mandolin, saxophone and piano. For this event we will only be hearing his acoustic from his vast catalogue with a little mix of classic rock and Country which is what you can find him doing with his band 5 in the Wheel. Visit their website fiveinthewheel.com

You can hear and see Dan Shaw LIVE in our Living Room Concert Series, this Friday at 5:30pm right here on PrescottENews
